{#-
  Shared guidance for the foundry cheatcodes RAG tools
  (foundry_cheatcodes_manual_search / foundry_cheatcodes_keyword_search /
  foundry_cheatcodes_get_section).
-#}
* `foundry_cheatcodes_manual_search(query, ...)` -- natural-language (semantic) search
  across the foundry cheatcodes documentation. Use this instead of guessing cheatcode
  names or signatures; prefer it for conceptual questions ("how do I mock an external
  call?").
* `foundry_cheatcodes_keyword_search(query, ...)` -- full-text search over the same
  documentation. Prefer it when you already know the identifier or exact phrase you
  are looking for; it returns matching section titles to feed into
  `foundry_cheatcodes_get_section`.
* `foundry_cheatcodes_get_section(section_names)` -- fetch a cheatcode page in full
  when you need its parameters / examples / gotchas.
